      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CENTAUREA (2) broke from the inside draw and filled a minor placing last start, beaten only one length (26.68) behind Pepper Pie at Warragul. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Key chance in this line up. MARSHAL LEE ROSE (8) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fifth (24.94) in a Mix 6/7 at this track. Warrants plenty of respect. WAX OFF (7) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (22.52) at Warragul behind Mr. Mocha in a Mix 6/7. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Expecting another good run. BRINDLE MOTION (4) was out of the frame here most recently but can atone.",
